
[1]cavalier

   CAVALIER, n.

   1. A horseman, especially an armed horseman; a knight.

   2. A gay, sprightly, military man.

   3. The appellation of the party of king Charles I.

   4. In fortification, an elevation of earth, situated ordinarily in the
   gorge of a bastion, bordered with a parapet, with embrasures.

   5. In the manege, one who understands horsemanship; one skilled in the
   art of riding.

                                CAVALIER, a.

   1. Gay; sprightly; warlike; brave; generous.

   2. Haughty; disdainful.
